title: Kentucky at Mississippi State at 7:30 p.m. ET Kickoff on SEC Network
text:
Kentucky at Mississippi State at 7:30 p.m. ET Kickoff on SEC Network Posted: Mon 1:26 PM, Oct 12, 2015 / Headlines List / Article 
LEXINGTON, Ky. – Kentucky’s football game at Mississippi State has been selected for a 7:30 p.m. ET kickoff with the game televised live on the SEC Network, it was announced by the Southeastern Conference on Monday afternoon. 
Kentucky (4-1, 2-1 SEC) will face off with Mississippi State (4-2, 1-2 SEC) at 7:30 p.m. ET in Starkville, Miss., on Oct. 24. 
The Wildcats will return to the field on Thursday with a primetime matchup with Auburn at The New Commonwealth Stadium. Kickoff is slated for 7 p.m. and the game will be televised live on ESPN and broadcast live on the UK Sports Radio Network.
